entries.femaleVariant: Looking for a braindance.
Looking for a braindance.
V, nice surprise.
Listen, I've seen what you can do. You've earned my respect. And I want you earning more of my eddies.
So here's what's going to happen. I'll get you what you want, just look out for a package.
Thanks, Wako. Where'll the pick-up be?
No, but I have a pretty good idea who can.
What is it you need?
How are things?
How's things, Wako?
This a prelude to whatever illegal favor you're about to ask me?
What? Never...
In that case, they couldn't be better. Kind of you to ask. And you?
Uh, any particular one?
Logo on the casing – a Death's Head moth.
Whoa, now, that's quicksand, so I would advise caution…
Can you get me one?
Know who makes 'em?
Can you get me one of those recordings?
Know who makes 'em? Where they scroll 'em?
And do you know what a fixer does? Allow me to explain.
Not only do I finalize transactions. I can accomplish the goddamn impossible.
Makin' sure the buyer, supplier, and ever-neglected intermediary not only keep their heads in their games but keep their heads. Period.
Which would be?
I'll have my guy drop it off in a secure location. Sending you the coordinates now.
There's a store on Jig-Jig Street, it has a pandora's box worth of crap inside. Try asking the owner.
Who'd that be?
Thanks, Wako.
So don't you ever ask me who, with whom, where, when, why and how.
